obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24213)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "(Conditions of Service)" (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24213&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Supreme Court Judges ^1`
  line `[(Salaries and Conditions of`
  line `Service)] Act, 1958.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24214)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24214&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,―`
  line
  line `(a) “acting Chief Justice” means a Judge appointed under article 126 of the Constitution to`
  line `perform the duties of the Chief Justice of India;`
  line
  line `(b) “actual service” includes―`
  line
  line `(i) time spent by a Judge on duty as a Judge, or in the performance of such other functions`
  line `as he may, at the request of the President, undertake to discharge; and`
  line
  line `(ii) vacations;`
  line
  line `(c) “Chief Justice” means the Chief Justice of India, but does not include an acting Chief`
  line Justice;
  line
  line `(d) “High Court” means the High Court for a State;`
  line
  line `(e) “Judge” means a Judge of the Supreme Court and includes the Chief Justice and an acting`
  line `Chief Justice;`
  line
  line `(f) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) “service as a Judge in India” means service rendered ^1`
  line `[in the Supreme Court] and in one`
  line `or more of the High Courts, and “Judge in India” and “service for pension as a Judge in India”`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(h) “service for pension” includes―`
  line
  line `(i) actual service;`
  line
  line `(ii) time spent by a Judge of a High Court in attending the sittings of the Supreme Court`
  line `as an ad hoc Judge under article 127 of the Constitution, if he is subsequently appointed as a`
  line `Judge:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(iii) the amount, actually taken, of each period of leave on full allowances at a rate equal`
  line `to the monthly rate of the salary;]`
  line
  line `(i) “vacation” means such period or periods during a year as may be fixed as vacation by or`
  line `under the rules of the Supreme Court made with the prior approval of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 18, for certain words (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 57 of 1980, s. 7, for sub-clause (iii) (w.e.f. 10-12-1980).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24215)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Kinds of leave admissible to a Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24215&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, leave granted`
  line `to a Judge may be at his option either―`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) leave on full allowances (including commuted leave on half allowances into leave on full`
  line `allowances on medical certificate); or]`
  line
  line `(b) leave on half allowances; or`
  line
  line `(c) leave partly on full allowances and partly on half allowances.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Chapter, any period of leave on full allowances shall be reckoned as`
  line `double that period of leave on half allowances.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) For the purposes of this Chapter, casual leave may be admissible to a Judge in a calendar`
  line `year, for such number of days and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 77 of 1971, s. 2, for clause (a) (w.e. f. 15-1-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 19 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24216)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Leave account showing the amount of leave due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24216&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A leave account shall be kept for each`
  line `Judge showing therein the amount of leave due to him in terms of leave on half allowances.`
  line
  line `(2) In the leave account of a Judge―`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be credited to him―`
  line
  line `(i) one-fourth of the time spent by him on actual service; ^1`
  line ***
  line
  line `(ii) where the Judge, by reason of his having been detained for the performance of duties`
  line `not connected with the Supreme Court, cannot enjoy any vacation which he would otherwise`
  line `have been entitled to enjoy had he not been so detained, as compensation for the vacation not`
  line `enjoyed, a period equal to double the period by which the vacation enjoyed by him in any`
  line `year falls short of one month;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(iii) where the Judge was, prior to his appointment as such, a Judge of a High Court, the`
  line `period of leave earned by him as a Judge of the High Court, ^3`
  line `***; and]`
  line
  line `(b) there shall be debited to him all leave with allowances taken by him.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall be deemed to have come into force on the 1st day of May, 1958.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and" omitted by Act 77 of 1971, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-5-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-5-1958).`
  line
  line `3. The certain words omitted by Act 7 of 1999, s. 7 (w.e.f. 8-1-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (24217)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Leave encashment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24217&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[4A. Leave encashment.―A Judge shall be entitled in his entire service, including the period of`
  line `service rendered either as a Judge of a High Court or in a pensionable post under the Union or a State`
  line `or on re-employment, if any, to claim the cash equivalent of leave salary on his retirement`
  line ^2
  line `[in respect`
  line `of the period of leave at his credit, calculated on full allowances basis,] to the extent of the maximum`
  line `period prescribed for encashment of such leave under the All India Service (Leave) Rules, 1955.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-1-1999).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 20, for "in respect of the period of earned leave at his credit" (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24218)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Aggregate amount of leave which may be granted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24218&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The aggregate amount of leave`
  line `which may be granted to a Judge during the whole period of his service as such shall not exceed in`
  line `terms of leave on half allowances three years ^1`
  line `[including the period credited to his leave account`
  line `under sub-section (2) (a) (iii) of section 4 as leave earned by him as a Judge of a High Court] together`
  line `with the aggregate of the periods, if any, credited to his leave account under sub-section (2) (a) (ii) of`
  line `section 4 as compensation for vacation not enjoyed.`
  line
  line `(2) The aggregate amount of leave on full allowances which may be granted to a Judge during the`
  line `whole period of his service as such shall not exceed one-twenty-fourth of the period spent by him on`
  line `actual service together with one-half of the aggregate periods, if any, ^2`
  line `[credited to his leave account―`
  line
  line `(a) under sub-section (2) (a) (ii) of section 4 as compensation for vacation not enjoyed, and`
  line
  line `(b) under sub-section (2) (a) (iii) of section 4 as leave earned by him as a Judge of a High`
  line Court.]
  line
  line `(3) ^3`
  line `[Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 5A, the maximum period of leave`
  line `which may be granted] at one time shall be, in the case of leave on full allowances, five months and in`
  line `the case of leave with allowances of any kind, sixteen months.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 77 of 1971, s. 4 (w.e.f. 17-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "credited to his leave account under sub-section (2) (a) (ii) of section 4 as compensation for`
  line `vacation not enjoyed" (w.e.f. 17-10-1958).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "The maximum period of leave which may be granted" (w.e.f. 17-10-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (24219)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 7
  title `Commutation of leave on half allowances into leave on full allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-1-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24219&sectionno=5A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line ^5
  line `[5A. Commutation of leave on half allowances into leave on full allowances.―(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of section 5, a Judge may be permitted to`
  line `commute leave on half allowances into leave on full allowances on medical certificate up to a`
  line `maximum of three months during the whole period of his leave as a Judge.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the maximum period of leave on full allowances which may be granted at one`
  line `time to a Judge under sub-section (3) of section 5, the amount of commuted leave permitted to him`
  line `under this section shall not be taken into account.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24220)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Grant of leave not due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24220&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the maximum limit specified in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 5, leave on half allowances may be granted to a Judge in excess of the amount at his credit―`
  line
  line `(i) on medical certificate; or`
  line
  line `(ii) otherwise than on medical certificate, for a period not exceeding six months, or for two or`
  line `more periods not exceeding in the aggregate six months, during the whole period of his service as`
  line `a Judge:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such leave shall be granted if the Judge is not expected to return to duty at the`
  line `end of such leave and earn the leave granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24221)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Special disability leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24221&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Special disability leave may be granted to a Judge under such`
  line `circumstances, on such allowances and for such periods as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24222)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Extraordinary leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24222&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Extraordinary leave may be granted to a Judge for a period not`
  line `exceeding six months, or for two or more periods not exceeding in the aggregate six months, during the whole period of his service as a Judge in excess of any leave permissible under the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, but no salary or allowances shall be payable in respect of such leave.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24223)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Leave allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 21, for section 9 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24223&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Leave allowances.―The monthly rate of leave salary payable to a Judge shall be in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 3.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24224)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Combining leave with vacation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24224&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `A Judge may be permitted to combine vacation on full`
  line `salary with leave, if―`
  line
  line `(a) where the vacation consists of one continuous period, the leave is taken either at the`
  line `commencement or at the end of the vacation but not at both;`
  line
  line `(b) where the vacation is divided into two periods, the leave is taken for the interval, or part of`
  line `the interval, between the two periods of that vacation, or for the interval, or part of the interval,`
  line `between the second period of that vacation and the commencement of the next ensuing vacation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such permission to combine vacation with leave shall be granted, if it becomes`
  line `necessary to appoint an acting Chief Justice during the period of vacation or if the Judge is not`
  line `expected to return to duty at the end of such leave.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24225)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Consequences of over staying leave or vacation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24225&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a Judge overstays his leave or any`
  line `vacation, whether combined with leave or not, he shall receive no salary in respect of the period of his`
  line `absence in excess of the leave granted to him or beyond the end of the vacation, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if such absence is due to circumstances beyond his control, the period thereof may`
  line `be treated as leave and may be debited to his leave account.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this Act shall be construed as requiring a Judge to rejoin on the expiration of the`
  line `period of leave when that period expires immediately before the commencement of a vacation, nor as`
  line `authorising any acting Chief Justice to continue to hold the acting appointment during the vacation.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24226)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Authority competent to grant leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24226&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The authority competent to grant or refuse leave to a`
  line `Judge or to revoke or curtail the leave already granted to a Judge shall be the President who shall`
  line `exercise the power after consultation with the Chief Justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (24227)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 15
  title `Salaries of the Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24227&sectionno=12A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 ^2`
  line `[12A. Salaries of the Judges.―(1) There shall be paid to the Chief Justice of India, by way of`
  line `salary, ^3`
  line [
  line ^4
  line `[two lakh eighty thousand rupees per mensem]].`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be paid to a Judge of the Supreme Court, by way of salary, ^5`
  line [
  line ^6
  line `[two lakh fifty`
  line `thousand rupees per mensem] ].`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1998, s. 7, for the heading "PENSIONS" (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 2009, s. 8, for "thirty-three thousand rupees per mensem" (w.e.f. 1-1-2006).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2018, s. 6, for "one lakh rupees per mensem" (w.e.f. 1-1-2016).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2009, s. 8, for "thirty thousand rupees per mensem" (w.e.f. 1-1-2006).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 2018, s 6, for "ninety thousand rupees per mensem" (w.e.f. 1-1-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24228)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Pension payable to Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24228&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, a pension shall be payable`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of Part I of the Schedule to a Judge of the Supreme Court on his`
  line `retirement if, but only if,―`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) he has attained the age of sixty-five years; or`
  line
  line `(c) his retirement is medically certified to be necessitated by ill-health.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Explanation.―In this section, "Judge" means a Judge who has not held any other`
  line `pensionable post under the Union or a State and includes a person who was in service as a Judge on`
  line `the 20th May, 1954, and also includes a Judge having held any other pensionable post under the`
  line `Union or a State, who has elected to receive the pension payable under Part I of the Schedule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (a) omitted by Act 46 of 2005, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 22, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (24229)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 17
  title `Benefit of added years of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 2005, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24229&sectionno=13A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[13A. Benefit of added years of service.―Subject to the provisions of this Act, a period of ten`
  line `years shall be added to the service of a Judge for the purposes of his pension, who qualified for`
  line `appointment as such judge under sub-clause (b) of clause (3) of article 124 of the Constitution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24230)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 18
  title `Special provisions for pension in respect of Judges who are members of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24230&sectionno=14&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)`
  line `Every Judge who has held any other pensionable post under the Union or a State shall, on his`
  line `retirement, be paid a pension in accordance with the provisions of Part III of the Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such Judge shall elect to receive the pension payable to him either under`
  line `Part I of the Schedule, or as the case may be, Part III of the Schedule, and the pension payable to him`
  line `shall be calculated accordingly.]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), any Judge to whom that sub-section`
  line `applies and who is in service on or after the 1st day of October, 1974, may, if he has elected under the`
  line `proviso to that sub-section to receive the pension payable to him under ^3`
  line `*** Part III of the`
  line `Schedule before the date on which the Supreme Court Judges (Conditions of Service) Amendment`
  line `Act, 1976 (36 of 1976), receives the assent of the President, cancel such election and elect afresh to`
  line `receive the pension payable to him under Part I of the Schedule and any such Judge who dies before`
  line `the date of such assent, shall be deemed to have elected afresh to be governed by the provisions of the`
  line `said Part I if the provisions of that Part are more favourable in his case. ]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 23, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 36 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f 1-10-1974).`
  line
  line `3. The words and figures "Part II or, as the case may be," omitted by Act 13 of 2016, s. 23 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24231)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of President to add to the service for pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24231&sectionno=15&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The President may, for special`
  line `reasons, direct that any period not exceeding three months shall be added to the service for pension of`
  line `a Judge, and any such period so added shall count for pension purposes―`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a Judge who has served in the Supreme Court as Chief Justice, as service as`
  line `Chief Justice; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other Judge, as service as any other Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24232)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `Extraordinary pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24232&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Extraordinary pensions and gratuities may be granted to a Judge`
  line `under such circumstances and on such scales as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (24233)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 21
  title `Family pension and gratuity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24233&sectionno=16A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[16A. Family pension and gratuity.^2`
  line `[(1) Where a Judge who, being in service on or after the`
  line `commencement of the High Court and Supreme Court Judges (Conditions of Service) Amendment`
  line `Act, 1986 (38 of 1986),`
  line
  line `(a) dies before retirement, ^3`
  line `[family pension calculated at the rate of fifty per cent. of his`
  line salary]
  line ^4
  line `*** on the date of his death shall be payable to the person or persons entitled thereto and`
  line `the amount so payable shall be paid from the day following the date of death of the Judge for a`
  line `period of seven years or for a period up to the date on which the Judge would have attained the`
  line `age of sixty-five years, had he survived, whichever is earlier, ^5`
  line `[and thereafter at the rate of thirty`
  line `per cent. of his salary] ^6`
  line `***; and`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(b) dies after retirement on attaining the age of sixty-five years, ^8`
  line `[family pension shall be`
  line `thirty per cent. of his salary]`
  line ^4
  line `*** and shall be payable to the person or persons entitled thereto;`
  line
  line `(c) dies after retirement after seeking premature retirement and before attaining the age of`
  line `sixty-five years, family pension shall be calculated at the rates specified in clause (a) shall be`
  line `payable to the person or persons entitled thereto.]`
  line
  line ^9
  line `[Provided that in no case the amount of family pension calculated under this sub-section shall`
  line `exceed the pension payable to the Judge under this Act.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of determining the person or persons entitled to family pension`
  line `under this sub-section,`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a Judge who elects or is eligible to receive pension under Part I of the`
  line `Schedule, the rules, notifications and orders for the time being in force with regard to the person`
  line `or persons entitled to family pension in relation to an officer of the Central Civil Services,`
  line `Group A, shall apply;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a Judge who elects to receive pension under ^10`
  line `* * * Part III of the Schedule,`
  line `the ordinary rules of his service if he had not been appointed a Judge with respect to the person or`
  line `persons entitled to family pension shall apply and his service as a Judge being treated as service`
  line therein.]
  line
  line `(2) The rules, notifications and orders for the time being in force with respect to the grant of`
  line `death-cum-retirement gratuity benefit to or in relation to an officer of the Central Civil Services,`
  line `Class I (including the provisions relating to deductions from pension for the purpose) shall apply to or`
  line `in relation to the grant of death-cum-retirement gratuity benefit to or in relation to a Judge who, being`
  line `in service on or after the 1st day of October, 1974, retires, or dies in circumstances to which`
  line `section 16 does not apply, subject to the modifications that`
  line
  line `(i) the minimum qualifying service for the purpose of entitlement to the gratuity shall be two`
  line `years and six months;`
  line
  line `(ii) the amount of gratuity shall be calculated on the basis of ^11`
  line `[ten days] salary for ^12[each`
  line `completed six months period] of service as a Judge;`
  line ^13***
  line
  line ^14
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line Explanation.^15
  line `[In sub-section (2)], the expression Judge has the same meaning as in`
  line `section 13.]`
  line
  line `^16]Explanation@i/@.—For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that any entitlement for additional quantum of pension or family pension shall be, and shall be deemed always to have been, from the first day of the month in which the pensioner or family pensioner completes the age specified in the first column of the scale.]br`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1976, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1986, s. 8, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f.1-11-1986).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 8 of 2003, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 01.01.1996).`
  line
  line `4. The words plus fifty per cent. of his dearness pay omitted by Act 23 of 2009, s. 9 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 8 of 2003, s. 2, for and thereafter at the rate of half of the family pension so admissible (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `6. The words plus thirty per cent. of his dearness pay omitted by Act 23 of 2009, s. 9 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 1989, s. 7, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 30-8-1989).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 8 of 2003, s. 2, for family pension shall be thirty per cent. of the pension eligible (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `9. The proviso ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `10. The words and figures Part II or omitted by Act 13 of 2016, s. 24 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 7 of 1999, s. 9, for twenty days (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for each completed year (w.e.f. 1-1-1996).`
  line
  line `13. The word and omitted by Act 20 of 1988, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-1-1986).`
  line
  line `14. Clause (iii) omitted by Act 20 of 1988, s. 5. (w.e.f. 1-1-1986).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 38 of 1986, s. 8, for In this section (w.e.f. 1-11-1986).`
  line
  line `16. Explanation ins. by Act 44 of 2021, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-12-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_b:
  sectionId (24234)
  sectionNo 16B
  orderNo 22
  title `Additional quantum of pension or family pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24234&sectionno=16B&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_16_b_content:
  string
  line `^3[16B. Additional quantum of pension or family pension.Every retired Judge or after his`
  line `death, the family, as the case may be, shall be entitled to an additional quantum of pension or family`
  line `pension in accordance with the following scale:--`
  line
  line __________________________________________________________________________________
  line `Age of Pensioner or family Pensioner Additional quantum of pension or family pension`
  line
  line __________________________________________________________________________________
  line `From eighty years to less than eighty-five years Twenty per cent. of basic pension or family`
  line pension
  line
  line `From eighty-five years to less than ninety years Thirty per cent. of basic pension or family`
  line pension
  line
  line `From ninety years to less than ninety-five years Forty per cent. of basic pension or family`
  line pension
  line
  line `From ninety-five years to less than hundred years Fifty per cent. of basic pension or family`
  line pension
  line
  line `From hundred years or more Hundred per cent. of basic pension or family`
  line pension.]
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that any entitlement for additional quantum of pension or family pension shall be, and shall be deemed always to have been, from the first day of the month in which the pensioner or family pensioner completes the age specified in the first column of the scale.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 23 of 2009, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-1-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Explanation ins. by Act 44 of 2021, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-12-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (24235)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 23
  title `Pension payable to a Judge who was in receipt of pension at the time of appointment as such.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24235&sectionno=17&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `If, at the time of his appointment to the Supreme Court, a Judge is in receipt of a pension in`
  line `respect of any previous service either as a Judge of a High Court or in any other pensionable civil post`
  line `under the Union or a State, the pension payable to him under this Act shall be an additional pension`
  line `for service in the Supreme Court equal to the difference between his original pension and the pension`
  line `to which he would have been entitled under this Act, if his service in the Supreme Court had been`
  line `rendered in continuation of the previous service for which his original pension was granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (24236)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 24
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24236&sectionno=18&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `[Conversion of sterling pension into rupees.] Omitted by the High Court and the`
  line `Supreme Court Judges (Salaries and Conditions of Service) Amendment Act, 2016 (13 of 2016), s. 25`
  line `(w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (24237)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 25
  title `Commutation of pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24237&sectionno=19&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Civil Pensions (Commutation) Rules for the time being in`
  line `force shall, with necessary modifications, apply to Judges.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (24238)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 26
  title `Provident fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. The words "is a member of the Indian Civil Service or" omitted by Act 13 of 2016, s. 26 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24238&sectionno=20&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Every Judge shall be entitled to subscribe to the General Provident Fund`
  line `(Central Services):`
  line
  line `Provided that a Judge who ^1`
  line `*** has held any other pensionable civil post under the Union or a`
  line `State shall continue to subscribe to the provident fund to which he was subscribing before his`
  line `appointment as a Judge:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a Judge who was appointed before the commencement of this Act may`
  line `continue to subscribe to the provident fund to which he was subscribing immediately before such`
  line commencement.
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (24239)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 27
  title `Deposit Linked Insurance Scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 1986, s. 9 (w.e.f. 5-9-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24239&sectionno=20A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[20A. Deposit Linked Insurance Scheme.―The Deposit Linked Insurance Scheme for the time`
  line `being in force under the General Provident Fund (Central Services) Rules, 1960, shall apply to every`
  line `Judge whether he subscribes to the General Provident Fund (Central Services) or any other Provident`
  line `Fund referred to in section 20.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (24240)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 28
  title `Authority competent to grant pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24240&sectionno=21&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Save as may be otherwise expressly provided in`
  line `the relevant rules relating to the grant of extraordinary pensions and gratuities, the authority`
  line `competent to grant pension to a Judge under the provisions of this Act shall be the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (24241)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 29
  title `Travelling allowance to a Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24241&sectionno=22&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `A Judge shall receive such reasonable allowance to`
  line `reimburse him for expenses incurred in travelling on duty within the territory of India and shall be`
  line `afforded such reasonable facilities in connection with travelling as may, from time to time, be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (24242)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 30
  title `Facilities for rent-free houses and other conditions of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24242&sectionno=23&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Judge shall be`
  line `entitled without payment of rent to the use of an official residence in accordance with such rules as`
  line `may, from time to time, be made in this behalf.`
  line
  line ^1
  line [
  line ^2
  line `[(1A) Where a Judge does not avail himself of the use of an official residence, he may be paid`
  line `every month an allowance equivalent to an amount of twenty-four per centum of the salary which`
  line `shall be increased at the rate of—`
  line
  line `(a) twenty-seven per centum, when Dearness Allowance crosses twenty-five per centum; and`
  line
  line `(b) thirty per centum, when Dearness Allowance crosses fifty per centum.] ^3`
  line ***]].
  line
  line `(2) Every Judge and the members of his family shall be entitled to such facilities for medical`
  line `treatment and for accommodation in hospitals as may, from time to time, be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The conditions of service of a Judge for which no express provision has been made in this Act`
  line `shall be such as may be determined by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(4) Sub-sections (1), (2) and (3) shall be deemed to have come into force on the 26th day of`
  line `January, 1950 and sub-section (1A) shall be deemed to have come into force on the 9th day of`
  line `May, 1986 and any rule made under any of the said sub-sections may be made so as to be`
  line `retrospective to any date not earlier than the commencement of the respective sub-section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 1993, s. 2 (w.e.f. 26-12-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2018, s. 7 for "sub section (1A)" (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `3. The words "plus thirty per cent. of the dearness pay" omitted by Act 23 of 2009, s. 11 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 72 of 1993, s. 2 (w.e.f. 26-12-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (24243)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 31
  title `Conveyance facilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24243&sectionno=23A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line [
  line ^2
  line `[23A. Conveyance facilities.―Every Judge shall be entitled to a staff car and ^3`
  line `[two hundred`
  line `litres of fuel every month or the actual consumption of fuel] per month, whichever is less.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1986, s. 10, for section 23A (w.e.f. 1-11-1986).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1996, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 11-1-1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b:
  sectionId (24244)
  sectionNo 23B
  orderNo 32
  title `Sumptuary allowance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24244&sectionno=23B&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[23B. Sumptuary allowance-- The Chief Justice and each of the other Judges shall be entitled to`
  line `a sumptuary allowance of ^2[^3[forty-five thousand] ] rupees per month and ^4[^5[thirty-four thousand]]`
  line `rupees] per month respectively`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2009, s. 12, for "ten thousand" (w.e.f.16-3-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2018, s. 8, for "twenty thousand" (w.e.f. 22-9-2017).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2009, s. 12, for "seven thousand five hundred" (w.e.f. 16-3-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2018, s. 8, for "fifteen thousand" (w.e.f. 22-9-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_c:
  sectionId (24245)
  sectionNo 23C
  orderNo 33
  title `Medical facilities for retired Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content
  footnotes `1. 1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-10-1974)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24245&sectionno=23C&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[23C. Medical facilities for retired Judges.-- Every retired Judge shall, with effect from the date`
  line `on which the Supreme Court Judges (Conditions of Service) Amendment Act, 1976 (36 of 1976)`
  line `receives the assent of the President, be entitled, for himself and his family, to the same facilities as`
  line `respects medical treatment and on the same conditions as a retired officer of the Central Civil`
  line `Services, Class I and his family, are entitled under any rules and orders of the Central Government for`
  line `the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_d:
  sectionId (24246)
  sectionNo 23D
  orderNo 34
  title `Exemption from liability to pay Income-tax on certain perquisites received by a Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24246&sectionno=23D&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line [
  line ^2
  line `[23D. Exemption from liability to pay Income-tax on certain perquisites received by a`
  line `Judge.―Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961),―`
  line
  line `(a) the value of rent-free official residence provided to a Judge under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 23 ^3[or the allowance paid to him under sub-section (1A) of that section];`
  line
  line `(b) the value of the conveyance facilities provided to a Judge under section 23A;`
  line
  line `(c) the sumptuary allowance provided to a Judge under section 23B,`
  line
  line `shall not be included in the computation of his income chargeable under the head “Salaries” under`
  line `section 15 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).]`
  line
  line `^4[(d) the value of leave travel concession provided to a Judge and members of his family.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1980, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1988, s. 6, for section 23D (w.e.f. 1-11-1986).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 72 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 9-5-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 2 of 1994, s. 3 (w.e.f. 4-1-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (24247)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24247&sectionno=24&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:―`
  line
  line `(a) leave of absence of a Judge, including special disability leave;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) the number of casual leaves and the conditions subject to which it may be allowed`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 3;]`
  line
  line `(b) pension payable to a Judge, including extraordinary pensions and gratuities;`
  line
  line `(c) travelling allowances to a Judge;`
  line
  line `(d) use of official residence by a Judge;`
  line
  line `(e) facilities for medical treatment and other conditions of service of Judge;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2016, s. 27 (w.e.f. 5-4-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1976, s. 5, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-10-1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (24248)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 36
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514&sectionId=24248&sectionno=25&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00002_195841_1517807317514
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall have effect so as to give to a Judge who is`
  line `serving as such at the commencement of this Act less favourable terms in respect of his privileges and`
  line `allowances or his rights in respect of leave of absence (including leave allowances) or pension than`
  line `those to which he would have been entitled, if this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
